span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How does decentralized editing work</span>?\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editing process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The reputation of all users is then used by the algorithm to understand which contribution(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) was valuable to editing process, tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way. This means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth (almost) genuine money - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span>Our end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control, and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end.\r\nAt the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens.\r\nWider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What are Magazine tokens good for?</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. But s</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ince we don’t like ads, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How do I participate?\r\n</span>First thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree you find them relevant or insightful, share them on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such actions is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will rewarded with tokens and your reputation increases.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How does the reputation system work?\r\n</span>Reputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to confirm to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree then those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here </a>and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What\'s the difference between reputation and token</span>?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-14 16:38:52','2016-02-14 16:38:52','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(384,8,'2016-02-14 17:17:36','2016-02-14 17:17:36','<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What is Backfeed?</span>\r\nBackfeed is an opensource start up that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration.\r\nOur goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures.\r\nBackfeed provides the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve created among themselves according to contribution.\r\nThe core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What is the BACKFEED Magazine? </span>\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>We are a decentralized magazine</strong>, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and anyone who’s interested in contributing. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because it’s worth it!</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sM5i40u3LJO6_xI0w7i7F6QUHKGxm5tsLwXSOzeARIQ/edit#bookmark=id.ub1ft122675x\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">how and when</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> this happens.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How does decentralized editing work</span>?\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editing process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to editing process, tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way. This means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth (almost) genuine money - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\nAt this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be add later this year.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span>Our end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control, powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end.\r\nAt the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens.\r\nWider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What are Magazine tokens good for?</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. But s</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ince we don’t like ads, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How do I participate?\r\n</span>First thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How does the reputation system work?\r\n</span>Reputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to confirm to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree then those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here </a>and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens</span>?\r\n<b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> represents your influence on the editing process, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are your share of the value we’ve created together, </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">they signify how useful your input was to the editing process.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tokens</strong> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. <strong>Reputation</strong> is non-transferable and user specific.\r\n<strong>Tokens</strong> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. <strong>Reputation</strong>, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Why is my reputation so low?\r\n</span>Reputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-14 17:17:36','2016-02-14 17:17:36','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(385,8,'2016-02-15 10:23:07','2016-02-15 10:23:07','<div><code>[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]</code></div>\r\n<div><code> </code></div>\r\n<div><code>   [agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]</code></div>\r\n<div><code>Backfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve created amongst themselves according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.</code></div>\r\n<div><code>   [/agg_accordion_item]</code></div>\r\n<div><code> </code></div>\r\n<div><code>  [agg_accordion_item title=\"Title 1\"]</code></div>\r\n<div><code>      Item Content 2</code></div>\r\n<div><code>   [/agg_accordion_item]</code></div>\r\n<div><code>  </code></div>\r\n<div><code>   [agg_accordion_item title=\"Title 1\"]</code></div>\r\n<div><code>      Item Content 3</code></div>\r\n<div><code>   [/agg_accordion_item]</code></div>\r\n<div><code> </code></div>\r\n<div><code>[/agg_accordion]</code></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Decentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>We are a decentralized magazine</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because it’s worth it!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">how and when</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> this happens.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How does decentralized editing work</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(almost) genuine money</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What are Magazine tokens good for?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. </span><b>But since we don’t like ads</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How do I participate?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How does the reputation system work?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so </span><a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here </span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and </span><a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">?\r\n</span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. </span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is non-transferable and user specific.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. </span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why is my reputation so low?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 10:23:07','2016-02-15 10:23:07','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(386,8,'2016-02-15 10:25:40','2016-02-15 10:25:40','[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]\r\n\r\nBackfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve created amongst themselves according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Title 1\"]\r\n\r\nItem Content 3\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<b>We are a decentralized magazine</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because it’s worth it!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">how and when</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> this happens.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How does decentralized editing work</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth </span><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(almost) genuine money</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What are Magazine tokens good for?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. </span><b>But since we don’t like ads</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How do I participate?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How does the reputation system work?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so </span><a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here </span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and </span><a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">here</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">?\r\n</span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. </span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is non-transferable and user specific.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. </span><b>Reputation</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why is my reputation so low?\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 10:25:40','2016-02-15 10:25:40','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(387,1,'2016-02-15 10:48:34','2016-02-15 10:48:34','[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]\r\n\r\nBackfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve created amongst themselves according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\nWe are a decentralized magazine, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nBecause it’s worth it!\r\n\r\nWe have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">how and when</a> this happens.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does decentralized editing work?\"]\r\n\r\nFrom the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\nThe reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.\r\n\r\nThis means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">(almost) genuine money</a> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.\r\n\r\nAt this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nOur end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What are Magazine tokens good for?\"]\r\n\r\nTokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.\r\n\r\nOne of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. <b>But since we don’t like ads</b>, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.\r\n\r\nHowever, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How do I participate?\"]\r\n\r\nFirst thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does the reputation system work?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens?\"]\r\n\r\n<b>Reputation</b> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. <b>Reputation</b> is non-transferable and user specific.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. <b>Reputation</b>, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why is my reputation so low?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion]','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 10:48:34','2016-02-15 10:48:34','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(389,8,'2016-02-15 10:57:05','2016-02-15 10:57:05','[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]\r\nBackfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\nWe are a decentralized magazine, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nBecause it’s worth it!\r\n\r\nWe have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">how and when</a> this happens.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does decentralized editing work?\"]\r\n\r\nFrom the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\nThe reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.\r\n\r\nThis means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">(almost) genuine money</a> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.\r\n\r\nAt this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nOur end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What are Magazine tokens good for?\"]\r\n\r\nTokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.\r\n\r\nOne of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. <b>But since we don’t like ads</b>, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.\r\n\r\nHowever, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How do I participate?\"]\r\n\r\nFirst thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does the reputation system work?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens?\"]\r\n\r\n<b>Reputation</b> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. <b>Reputation</b> is non-transferable and user specific.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. <b>Reputation</b>, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why is my reputation so low?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion]','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 10:57:05','2016-02-15 10:57:05','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(390,8,'2016-02-15 11:00:06','2016-02-15 11:00:06','[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]\r\nBackfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this topic and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\n<strong>We are a decentralized magazine</strong>, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nBecause it’s worth it!\r\n\r\nWe have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">how and when</a> this happens.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does decentralized editing work?\"]\r\n\r\nFrom the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\nThe reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.\r\n\r\nThis means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">(almost) genuine money</a> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.\r\n\r\nAt this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nOur end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What are Magazine tokens good for?\"]\r\n\r\nTokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.\r\n\r\nOne of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. <b>But since we don’t like ads</b>, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.\r\n\r\nHowever, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How do I participate?\"]\r\n\r\nFirst thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does the reputation system work?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens?\"]\r\n\r\n<b>Reputation</b> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. <b>Reputation</b> is non-transferable and user specific.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. <b>Reputation</b>, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why is my reputation so low?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion]','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 11:00:06','2016-02-15 11:00:06','',380,'http://magazine.backfeed.cc/380-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(391,8,'2016-02-15 11:02:04','2016-02-15 11:02:04','[agg_accordion multiselectable=\"false\"]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is Backfeed?\"]\r\nBackfeed is an open-source startup that develops a social operating system for decentralized organizations, allowing for massive open source collaboration without central administration. We provide the infrastructure for decentralized cooperation, allowing large groups to create collectively and  share the value they\'ve according to contribution. Our goal is to enable anyone, anywhere to effectively collaborate with their peers without having to erect fixed hierarchies and rigid structures. The core of our decentralized governance tools and value distribution algorithm is the BACKFEED protocol, about which you can learn <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What is the BACKFEED Magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nDecentralization is one of the most important topics of our time with vast implications for every branch of social live; be it technology, economics, politics or culture. As an organization which recognizes the importance of this subject, and identifies it as one of the key elements for a prosperous future, we regard it as our responsibility to promote a wide ranging discussion about decentralization, the blockchain space and models for a collaborative economy; and you\'re invited to participate.\r\n\r\n<strong>We are a decentralized magazine</strong>, which essentially means that editing, writing and curation functions are delegated to the Backfeed community - which consists of our authors, readers and you, to the degree to which you’re interested in contributing. You can submit articles, rate the work of others and lead the discussion on topics brought forward here.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why should I be part of the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nBecause it’s worth it!\r\n\r\nWe have a special algorithm that determines the value of each contribution - be it an article you’ve submitted, rating of such, an insightful comment or even the generation of traffic via shares and tweets. The value you’ve generated is transferred to you in form of Magazine-Tokens, which eventually might be worth real money. Read here <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">how and when</a> this happens.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does decentralized editing work?\"]\r\n\r\nFrom the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours, our algorithm calculates a reputation score for you. This score determines how impactful you are in the editorial process. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\nThe reputation of all users is used by the algorithm to understand which contributions(submitted articles, comments, up/down votes) were valuable to the editorial process; tokens are then distributed to whomever lent a hand in a fruitful way.\r\n\r\nThis means that even your opinions on our articles, your up and down votes and your comments are worth <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Fls1C2LlvqFiIZl0rHF2n50ETNSSBcxiKCdtYPuvBtQ/edit#bookmark=id.u1xq69t46uyt\">(almost) genuine money</a> - after all, they’re what curates and edits this magazine.\r\n\r\nAt this point in time, the information gathered in the crowd-editing process is used to curate our front page and to decide which article will appear where. Further, more extended decentralized editing functions will be added later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How decentralized is the BACKFEED magazine?\"]\r\n\r\nOur end goal is to run the BACKFEED magazine as a fully operational decentralized organization, governed and edited by a vibrant online community without any central point of control and powered by our protocol - which is designed exactly to this end. At the moment the only truly decentralized function is the homepage layout and curation, along with the reputation system for contributors and their compensation with Magazine-tokens. Wider editing functions, such as the screening and editing of articles pre-publishing, the placement of picture-art and the choice of headlines, are being currently developed and will be online later this year.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What are Magazine tokens good for?\"]\r\n\r\nTokens signify the value you’ve contributed to the Backfeed magazine in form of articles, ratings, comments and shares. They represent the stake you hold in the collective editing process of our crowd-sourced magazine.  At the moment they’re mainly symbolic, but we have serious plans to monetize them.\r\n\r\nOne of the obvious ways would be selling ads exclusively in exchange for tokens, which would mean that advertisers would have to purchase tokens from you in order to publish ads here - granting  them real monetary value. <b>But since we don’t like ads</b>, we’re currently looking for other creative ways to monetize tokens. Charging tokens as an access fee for various forms of premium content is an option - which, again, would require readers to purchase them from you, turning them to a value baring cryptocurrency.\r\n\r\nHowever, we strongly recommend holding on to your tokens. In the meantime, subscribe so we can keep you up to date on this topic.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How do I participate?\"]\r\n\r\nFirst thing to do is to register. After that, all that\'s left is your natural interaction with the magazine: Rate articles according to your taste and to the degree to which you find them relevant or insightful. Share items on social media, post comments, rate and respond to comments of others, and, if you\'re in the mood - submit your own article. Every such action is evaluated, and if it was helpful to the editorial process you will be rewarded with tokens and your reputation is likely to increase.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"How does the reputation system work?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is the measure of your alignment with the BACKFEED community. If your contributions are regarded as valuable by the community, your reputation increases, if they\'re seen as irrelevant, it decreases. - But that\'s not at all a reason to conform to the mainstream taste. On the contrary, if your taste deviates from the mainstream you might be the first one to spot an extraordinary contribution that was overseen by the crowd. Voting it up highlights it for the rest of the community, if it is then found to be useful, the algorithm compensates you to a much larger degree than those who just chase the herd. So be yourself and don\'t hesitate to express yourself.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about the reputation system and the BACKFEED protocol in general, you can do so <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/category/backfeed-101/\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://magazine.backfeed.cc/the-backfeed-protocol-an-introduction-for-mere-mortals/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"What\'s the difference between reputation and tokens?\"]\r\n\r\n<b>Reputation</b> represents your influence on the editorial process, it is calculated from the way you rate the work of others and from the way others rate yours. The more aligned you are with the backfeed community, the more influence you enjoy.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are your share of the value we’ve created together, they signify how useful your input was to the editorial process.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are a transferable unit of value and function as a currency which can be bought and sold. <b>Reputation</b> is non-transferable and user specific.\r\n\r\n<b>Tokens</b> are generated every time a contribution was identified as valuable. Their total amount is not fixed and increases as long as new value is added to the system. <b>Reputation</b>, in contrast, is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[agg_accordion_item title=\"Why is my reputation so low?\"]\r\n\r\nReputation is relative and fixed. There is a total amount of 100% influence in the system, of which your reputation represents the share you enjoy, so don\'t be upset if your rep. is only a fraction of a percent, this is pretty normal since, fortunately, we\'re a very large crowd.\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion_item]\r\n\r\n[/agg_accordion]','FAQ','','inherit','closed','closed','','380-revision-v1','','','2016-02-15 11:02:04','2016-02-15 11:02:04','',380,'http:/